Bluetongue, Greece
-------------------
Information received on 24 Dec 2010 from Mr Spiros Doudounakis,
Director, Animal Health Directorate, Directorate General of
Veterinary Services / Animal Health Directorate, Ministry of Rural
Development and Food, ATHENS, Greece

Summary

Report type: Follow-up report No. 11
Start date: 3 Nov 2008
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 5 Nov 2008
Report date: 23 Dec 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 24 Dec 2010
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: December 2001
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 16
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks: [6 outbreaks on] Lesvos, Voreio Aigaio [South Aegean periphery]
[For full details of each of the 6 outbreaks, including exact
location and numbers of susceptible animals/cases, please go to the above URL].

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 6
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 1907 / 90 / 46 / 0 / 0

